{
  "text": "I was really questioning more about the more basic cause of the disease rather than the mechanism of its transmission. I was going back to the root or thought which created the possibility of this disease. Could you shortly tell me if I'm correct in assuming that the general reduction of thought over the long time on planet Earth with respect to an understanding of the law of one created a condition in which this what we call disease could develop. Is this correct? I am Ra. This is correct and perceptive. You as questioner begin now to penetrate the outer teachings. The root cause in this particular society was not so much a umbilicose action, although there were, shall we say, tendencies, but rather the formation of a money system and a very active trading and development of those tendencies towards greed and power, thus the enslaving of entities by other entities and the misapprehension of the Creator within each entity.",
